cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please also cite SENTINEL v1 and v2 — see ATTRIBUTION.md."
title: "A2A Coupling Findings — Secondary Analysis of SENTINEL v2 and Preliminary Fan-out Sibling-Coupling Measurement"
abstract: "This repository combines a pre-registered secondary analysis of Jason Gagne's SENTINEL v2 Governance Effectiveness release with a preliminary measured A2A fan-out result from the DOP research archive. In the measured T2 topology, two downstream specialists with no direct dialogue channel still reached mean pairwise S4 = 0.366 across 31 windows, indicating sibling coupling through shared-broker context. The repository also documents a stricter related replication line and the typed-intent architectural repair framing."
